The paper deals with optimization of shortest path algorithms, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper discusses the use of bounded Dijkstra algorithm, which is a modification of the Dijkstra algorithm, and its application in overlay algorithms solving complex problems such as constrained shortest path and constrained minimum Steiner tree. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
